The paper discusses the implementation of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) on FPGAs, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and hardware design, which falls under the categories of systems and control (SY) and architecture (AR). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient design methodology, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (NE).
